name: Ψυχή / Ἔρως –  amours buées (Dancing Psyche)
description:
Psyche, a young maiden of great beauty, was loved by Love itself. Love promised to her eternity by her side on the condition that she will never try to know Love's face. Unfortunately, on the malicious advice of her jealous sisters, one night, Psyche brings a lamp to contemplate Love in sleep. A drop of oil fell, Love woke up and fled.
Long is the initiation of Psyche then, in the hands of a jealous Aphrodite but always secretly supported by Love. (...)

« Dance, Lalla, with nothing on but air : 
Sing, Lalla, 
wearing the sky. 

Look at this glowing day ! What clothes could be so beautiful, or more scared? »

Lalleshwari
